 again in mid september. I get a lot of tells from people who grouped with me then &quot;Wow! how did you level so fast?&quot; I dinged 55 last wednesday evening before I crashed and I did play some of my alts over the weekend. But it seems that in 55 my soloing days are gone. I joined a guild (im on Luclin server) because a friend was in it when I was in the teens. I never did get many groups with them and I never could find a group because everyone just goes to nexus and gets a C3 then feels they dont need an enchanter. There is the first problem. People thinking enchanters are about A) Clarity the cleric and B) Haste the tanks. Yes I know that those are two invaluable assets we provide for a group but it sinks back into the mindset that I have despised since Ive started playing EQ. That mindset is that EQ is like any other punch-em kick-em action game like Mortal Combat . The largest number of idiots Ive seen are all tanks.....and all they do is press the attack button and scream for the cleric to heal them. So enchanters are only there to make them attack faster and make the cleric heal faster. Very necessary yes but at lower levels (up to the mid 30s early 40s) they dont really appreciate the haste that level of enchanter can provide and get their mana regen from someone in nexus via C3. I saw so many groups go ahead and accept a wipe rather than to let me mezz. Now, they dont really feel the &quot;need&quot; for an enchanter the way they do for a cleric so when things get ugly I have had noone in the group help me out so I ate a lot of deaths. Ok that is to be expected....chanters are going to be on hate list big time if theyre doing their job. But that problem rolls over to when I do mezz, sometimes repeatedly, multiple adds and when they finish one mob they immediatly turn and whack the other, breaking mezz and getting me killed before I get a chance to mem blur it. I try to explain but they simply dont care because I am not critical to them.<br>
<br>
So there is where I diverged.......<br>
<br>
I started soloing around 20 something and got good at it. First I fear kited with pet then I charm kited. Other times I would just root and nuke and I would always get more xp than groups could provide cause I would get negative xp when they get me killed. I bought sow potions and C3 in nexus. I found a lot of chanters sympathetic towards lower level chanters and they didnt charge for the buff. (thanks Indite!) Quad kiting with gravity flux in OT was fun. Kiting in Dreadlands was a piece of cake. Then I took it to Burning Woods with similar effectivness. Now that Im almost 56th Ive spent a lot of time the past couple of weeks in planar PoP groups.<br>
<br>
Now the old problem comes back to haunt me. Those dumb tanks still havent learned squat. The groups as a whole are now a lot more amiable to having an enchanter because people need the slowing if no shaman is around and always need the hasting. Mezzing mobs is now essential because they hit so hard and fast. So I run into a couple groups that, sure enough, turn and whack a mezzed arachnid as soon as the treant is dead as Im still debuffing it and it spanks me good. I am not in a guild so I have to get pickup groups and its getting really hard to decide when to dump these people. Should I just keep an ignore list or should I try to educate? I grow so weary of having to explain the mezz and aggro process to a clueless 59th level monk. I dont wanna make enemies but I also dont wanna get frustrated and give up. What is your break off point when you get an uncooperative group?<br>
<br>
Any recommendations for a decent guild? I know a 65th enchanter who still isnt interested in guilds and I dont know how she handles it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luxxorautumnwood>LuxxorAutumnwood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(12/23/02 9:40:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When to dump a group? (kind of long....lot of bitching)</span><hr size=1> Don't bother explaining the mez and aggro stuff to the clueless people... it makes you look kinda clueless yourself as you have spells to increase aggro on the MA, decrease aggro on yourself, and mem-blur. And 9 times outta 10, if I'm getting hit all I have to do is stand still for a sec and maybe stun and back up a little bit to give the MA time to get it back off of me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Just be careful about tash+debuffing before the tank has control of it and you should be fine <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sinnjatorix>Sinnjatorix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#330000>(1/10/03 2:45:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://w1.853.telia.com/~u85304784/pics/eq/Stringius.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When to dump a group? (kind of long....lot of bitching)</span><hr size=1> Have to have the room for all those spells to.<br>
<br>
Did a pick up group in overthere with my cleric, had two tanks and a rogue in the group, the rogue and 1 warrior was very good about taunting before breaking mez(well rogue has no taunt but he stood behind mob waiting for war), the other warrior just smacked the mob but got sorted out by the other melees, as a cleric i prefer not to have to heal the symboled chanter, so if i can spare the mana i root the mob, if not able to before it rushes i throw my lvl 5 stun at the mob to give the chanter a few seconds to back up and tanks to regain aggro, works most of the time at my current lvl(34).<br>
<br>
Think at 50+ people should know about mezz/aggro and how to break it without getting chanter killed but i guess that is to much to ask, maybe i should continue to solo, made it to 29 so far <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sinnjatorix>Sinnjatorix</A> at: 1/10/03 1:47:59 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goanad>Goanad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#330000>(1/13/03 4:42:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When to dump a group? (kind of long....lot of bitching)</span><hr size=1> I disagree with the person who said not to try and explain stuff to melees. <br>
<br>
In many cases with POP especially, you have to give some basics otherwise you'll end up dead virtually 100 percent of the time. <br>
<br>
My most recent pet peeve involve other melee not understanding how to handle an add when and SK who is pulling has dotted the original mob. <br>
<br>
It escapes them how mezz won't land on the dotted mob(ie the mob that they are /assist) <br>
<br>
I'm getting to the point where, in such circumstances, I'm about to say &quot;screw it&quot; and just charm one of the mobs or root if it's rootable or whatever. /shrug <br>
