 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=478556"><img src=http://webpages.charter.net/mcanaday/sigtest2.jpg></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luxxorautumnwood>LuxxorAutumnwood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#330000>(1/15/03 2:48:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When to dump a group? (kind of long....lot of bitching)</span><hr size=1> Guess I have to say that I haven't really experienced many of the problems yall seem to be having, I'm on an older server where a lotta people have played a lot of classes and they know basics like don't pull with dots and such, esp by the time they've played any char over 60 levels or so.. kinda forgot that there are still a lotta people having their first go-round at it out there. Anyway, you usually won't have to keep all the aggro control spells memmed at once, it's more like you pick the method you like best and just use that one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iandamar>Iandamar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(1/15/03 8:32:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When do dump a group?</span><hr size=1> I had the same problem with a group in PoN, but I told them kinda harshly if they wanted to stay alive and have the cleric high on mana most of the time, and have not a lot of downtime, that they would have to listen to me.  I sounded like a complete ass but when they got the hang of it, they were glad they listened to me, they even thanked me for telling them that if they listen to the enchanter that things will go much more smoothly.  So don't worry about being an ass about it, just tell them nicely, if they don't listen be an ass, and if they still don't listen, thank them for the group and leave.  Well that's my input about this situation, hope it helps. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dirgeofhate>Dirge of Hate</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.uiuc.edu/ro/elysium/images/purfire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(1/17/03 10:59:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When do dump a group?</span><hr size=1> Well Here is my Rule. If the Group i am currently in don't mind mobs Beating the Crud out of me, IE Breaking Mez with No taunting, Then i have no issues just Hasting and Letting Tank get beat on by 3-4 mobs. I can Stun and Gate if i get In Trouble. if the Group can't Handle the Few simple steps it takes to taunt a Mob 2-3 times then they don't need Mezzing. I Can Solo with the Best of them. It's a Waist of my Time to join a Group just to Die with it. I am on Fennin Ro. People there Know better and Beleave it or Not one of the Worst Mez Breaking monks I have met is the Alt of a 60th Chanter. Go Figure. Same Chanter that I used to Hear Complaining in /gu about Tanks Breaking Mezz.. It's just Sad. Glad my 49th Pet and I get along so well. I Like to Group  just for the felling of power of Controlling Massive trains and saving the Group. Most times, if i can Get the monk to Sit down, I will Pull trains to the Group and then Mezz them off with they Single out Targets. Fast Xp and Keeps me Good and Busy. &quot; The Safest puller in the Game is a Good Monk. The Best puller in the Game is a Good Chanter.&quot;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=laeyakk>Laeyakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(1/20/03 3:23:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When do dump a group?</span><hr size=1> Do start charming.<br>
<br>
Use root on mez'd mobs, or on mobs that aggro you, or on dotted mobs.<br>
<br>
Request, then demand, that tanks taunt.<br>
<br>
Request they have a macro &quot;about to break mez on %T&quot;, so you can stand.<br>
<br>
Sit while tanks are /taunting mez'd mobs, and stand before they attack.<br>
<br>
Keep &quot;reoccuring amnesia&quot; or &quot;blanket of forgetfulness&quot; memed.  Tossing them on a mob does help.<br>
<br>
Train 7 groups how to work with you.  Explain that you might do some stuff a bit differently, and to bear with you.<br>
<br>
Find an ally in the group before ranting at them.  1 other clued person, forming a unified front, helps alot.<br>
<br>
Leave groups lacking clued people.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=oliudyen>Oliudyen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#330000>(1/21/03 2:57:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=121.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When do dump a group?</span><hr size=1> First, on Fennin Ro everyone knows, if they dont, they are stupid. You cant get to 56+ with out learning to do basics in a group unless you solo your way. if you solo you either 1) are twinked very well, 2) cant find groups, 3) get more exp soloing than in a group of 4) prefer not to have to deal with morons.<br>
<br>
#4 explains itself, #1 if you are twinked well you haev a main and should know better. #2 if you cant follow the rules there is no wonder you cant find a group. #3 why you in the group?<br>
<br>
