What I dont understand is how the heck you are still debuffing a mob in the time it takes to kill the first mob? Number 1 if you chain cast Tash, Cripple and Shiftless deeds on a mob, you should expect to die. My taunts will not keep up, plain and simple. And No I am not the tank that bashes taunt everytime it pops up either. I have all my spell messages up and wait until I see %t yawns or what ever you are casting atm. I can handle aggro very good for the most part. So basicly you need to be pauseing in between your cast of those three spells if you are doing them all yourself.<br>
<br>
Some steps to follow (and Im just a tank) - Mez Mob 2, Mez mob 3, etc. If you have more than 2 comeing on a regular basis Winds of Tash is great in that situation, Slow Mob 1, slow mob 2, slow mob 3, Cripple mob 1, Med. This should about get you to mob 1 dieing. So Stand the HECK up! The Tank should pick the mob that has been mez'd the longest or the one that flat out isnt mez'd. Thanks to the great taunt tanks have expect the mob to run over to you and smack you. NO RUNNING! Stand there and take it. Nothing pisses me more than taunting as soon as Mez breaks and waiting for taunt recycle, clicking it, then haveing the chanter move cuz they are getting beat on - guess what, you are taking another round of beatings! Over all it shouldnt be all that bad cuz if you remember earlier you slowed the mob!<br>
<br>
